Testimony: I lost my mom May 7,2020. I still can’t believe it happened. My mom was such a phenenomal woman, I would’nt be able to put her life and impact into words. The stories and love that she left behind. She only had two children, but she was a mother to many people in the music business and everywhere we went. I lost my mom during the pandemic sadly from Cxvid and miraculously was able to actually go to hospital to say goodbye. I am sharing this testimony because the last few years have been the hardest and some of the best years of my life. God never took his hand off me and life has dualities, but God is always going before us, with us, and behind us. I am so thankful that I have had the means to heal and beat to my own drum without the pressure to be hustling and performing constantly.  This is healing that will be ongoing. I am just happy that I can share what have been faced with the last few years. I pride myself on being transparent and a real person. We have too many imposters on the internet. I take my hat off to people that can be extremely candid on the Internet, I was about everything but this was different. My entire world turned upside down. But, time heals… 

I hope this post doesn’t trigger anyone. Grieving a parent is not for the faint of heart. If you are going through grief right now … take care of yourself and give the rest to God, I am a living testimony that joy will come in the morning. 

#testimony #testimonytime #mytestimony

#sundayreset - Happy Sunday! I know its been a while since I have truly commited to social media. The truth is I have been focused on what God wants me to do and how he wants me to do it. Right now & going forward those are the only things that are important to me. I was once a part of the #hustleculture where business, success, and everything else tied to it was an idol. It even took so much of my flesh dying for me to even say it out loud. 😮‍💨

My mission is clearer to me more than ever before. I have been working in the background to elimnate so much and God has revealed to me why I am so passionate about eating right, sleeping right, taking the right supplements and just so much more. This is all connected to being a vessel and a voice for God. God doesn’t promise that you won’t get sick, but he does promise that no matter what happens he will go before you and be with you. 

One of the many blessings we have is the will to make choices that make us better for God’s will on the earth. 

So I am going ask a serious question, when it comes to your health how would you rate how you take care of yourself as a vessel for God’s purpose ? Drop a 1-10 in the comments 10 being the highest. I am a 8. What about you? 👇🏾

🗣️Undeniable Favor‼️
